# Add the GPG key fingerprint(s) authorized to decrypt secrets/store/.
# One fingerprint per line. No leading 0x. 40-char (SHA-1) fingerprints.
#
# Example:
#   1A2B3C4D5E6F7A8B9C0D1E2F3A4B5C6D7E8F9A0B
#
# This file controls who can decrypt every entry under store/ EXCEPT
# the store/runner/ subtree (which uses .gpg-id.runner additively).
#
# To enable: replace this placeholder file with real fingerprints, then
# run `PASSWORD_STORE_DIR="$PWD/secrets/store" pass init -p / $(cat secrets/.gpg-id)`
# to re-encrypt the whole store under the listed keys.
#
# PLACEHOLDER-NO-KEY-CONFIGURED
